{
  "texts": [
    "Distributed vs. Cloud-Only Execution We next analyze how network RTT affects the performance of distributed speculative decoding.",
    "Figure 6 varies RTT while keeping all other system configurations fixed.",
    "At low RTT values, distributed execution outperforms cloud-only mode because edge drafts are generated concurrently with cloud verification, improving throughput.",
    "However, as RTT increases, the communication overhead of each speculative iteration grows, causing noticeable degradation.",
    "In contrast, cloudonly mode (where the target handles both drafting and verification locally) remains unaffected by network latency but suffers from lower parallelism at low RTTs."
  ]
}